      <!-- Key Insights -->
      <section class="mb-24">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">Key Insights From 12 Years</h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">🎯</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Constraint Forces Clarity</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              "Student startups only" (2015) forced specificity about what students actually need. Every successful pivot came from narrowing focus, not broadening it.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">🤝</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Mission Alignment = Operational Requirement</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Facebook VR drifted. Freshworks programs worked. When funders don't own the vision, things fall apart—not philosophically, but operationally.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">📊</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Build Systems, Not Services</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              "At scale, one person can't help a thousand people." Artisanal mentorship doesn't scale. Platforms, progression systems, and automation do.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">🔓</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Open Source = Competitive Moat</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Pupilfirst's open-source commitment built trust with universities and educators. Knowledge locked in proprietary systems benefits vendors, not learners.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">❓</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">The Right Question Changes Everything</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              "How do we help students start startups?" → "How do we help students become genuinely capable?" Small shift in question. Massive shift in product.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">🚀</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Technology Unlocks New Economics</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              AI doesn't just improve efficiency—it fundamentally changes unit economics. High-quality education at ₹999/month becomes sustainable at scale.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

